result.name: Honbo

reviews.text: One of the best burger places in HK. Juicy patty. Sweet potato fries were nice. A bit on the pricey side.

Honbo is a lesser known local burger joint on Sun Street in Wanchai. Stopped by recently and had good burger for lunch. Opening hours are 12-4pm (lunch) and 5-10pm (dinner) daily. 

Menu is a short list of standard burger types, a few sides and drinks. Burgers are grilled up and served quickly. Seating area is just three side wall tables and one communal style table for 6-8 people. Tables are turned over pretty quickly if you find the place full. 

My recent burger (4 oz.) was pretty good. Beef patty was grilled to medium well but retained good beef flavours. Toppings were fine, bun soft and warm. Sweet potato fries were fried nicely and taste just fine. In short, this was a simple but good burger, just want you want somedays. Will happily return on this basis.

Wow so glad I stumbled across this little haven of delivdeliciousness. Not kidding probably this nicest cheese burger I've EVER HAD. Patty succulent  bun light and fresh sauce finished the job off and the fries were great. Wish this place every success.

Pretty hole in the wall decent burger joint. Serves a tasty burger.

Probably one of the best hole-in-the-wall burger spots you’d find in Hong Kong. Not hole-in-the-wall prices though. Not insanely expensive but definitely no fast food prices here. Do yourself a favor and get the double, you’re already there.
